headline: Palo Alto Networks beats Q1 estimates, while guidance disappoints
summary: While topping its fiscal first quarter expectations, Palo Alto Networks (PANW) disappointed on the revenue guidance front. The cybersecurity company announced a two-for-one stock split that will go into effect on Monday, December 16. Seana Smith and Brad Smith report on Palo Alto's first quarter print and its ambitions within the cybersecurity landscape. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Palo Alto Stock Is Falling After Earnings Beat. Why This Metric’s Worrying Analysts.
summary: Palo Alto Networks   posted earnings that beat Wall Street’s estimates and raised its guidance for the year.  Billings declined 14% and missed expectations.  While it’s still trying to become the top cybersecurity platform—putting everything businesses need to defend themselves from an attack in one place—the worry is that it’s not generating new business fast enough.
